description.p:
In the above circuit, the structure and parameter of each component are set as follows:



    

1) RT1 and RT2: thermistor (PTC). The static resistance is less than 5Ω In normal temperature, the non-operating current is larger than 0.3 A, and when the operating current is 0.5 A in normal temperature, the operation time is larger than 30 s;

2) G1 and G2: two-electrode gas discharge tubes (GDT) with the FS function. The direct current breakdown voltage is not larger than 300 V, and the joint capacitance is smaller than 2 pF. The FS function is a fail-safe protection function, that is, when the GDT is enabled for a long time and becomes overheated, the FS is started and reliably short-circuits two poles of the GDT, to ensure the safe failure of the GDT.
